Here's a C++ program that reads a text file line by line and counts the number of occurrences of a specific word in the file:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>
#include <map>

int main() {
    std::ifstream file("filename.txt");
    std::string line;
    std::map<std::string, int> wordCount;
    std::string targetWord = "target_word"; // Replace with the word you want to search for.

    while (std::getline(file, line)) {
        std::size_t pos = line.find(targetWord);
        if (pos != std::string::npos) {
            wordCount[targetWord]++;
        }
    }

    for (auto const& pair : wordCount) {
        std::cout << pair.first << ": " << pair.second << "\n";
    }

    return 0;
}
```

This program reads a text file named "filename.txt" and searches for the specified target word. If the target word is found, it increments the count for that word in a map. Finally, it prints the count of each word found in the file. 

